def: Presenting hemihedral forms, in which all the sectants havehalt the whole number of planes. Dana.
A name given to the old Parthenon at Athens, because measuring100 Greek feet, probably in the width across the stylobate.
A switchboard in which connections are made by means of plugs.
The establishment or ascertaining of parentage; the assignmentof a child, as a bastard, to its father; filiation.
Anything that kills fungi.-- Fun`gi*ci"dal, n.
Of or pertaining to an urn; effected by an urn or urns. "Urnalinterments." Sir T. Browne.
The formation situated between the Permian and Lias, and sonamed by the Germans, because consisting of three series of strata,which are called in German the Bunter sandstein, Muschelkalk, andKeuper.
A bitter principle obtained from the dogbane (Apocynumcannabinum).
